{
  "texts": [
    "For instance, students can draw a circle and dynamically adjust it as they explore corresponding changes in its equation, or they can modify the equation of the circle to observe alterations in the geometry window.",
    "This exploratory aspect of learning enhances students' understanding of functional relationships, facilitating the introduction of new elements and rearrangements (Tomic, 2013).",
    "GeoGebra has emerged as a highly effective educational tool in classroom settings, highlighting the value of demonstration, modelling and collaborative group work approaches.",
    "By leveraging visualization techniques and intricate modeling capabilities, GeoGebra enables students to develop a deeper understanding of abstract mathematical concepts and establish meaningful connections with their personal experiences (Zulnaidi et al., 2020).",
    "Notably, the software has demonstrated particular efficacy in teaching calculus, as well as visualization-intensive subjects, such as geometry and algebra (Antohe, 2009; Haciomeroglu et al., 2009; Hohenwarter et al., 2008)."
  ]
}